Mountain Ski

by Patricia

document.documentElement.setAttribute('lang', 'en');
"Let's go to the Alps", your sister tells you, one day.
"The Alps?", you reply, surprised. "We haven't been there for years."
"I know", she says. "Don't you miss it? I do."
You think about it for a bit, and you have to admit she's right. As kids, you used to go with your family but, once your grandfather died, everyone seemed a little scared to go back.
"We used to have so much fun, remember?", she asks. "Remember how grandpa used to prank us? And that time mom was trying a ski trick, and grandpa said "You don't know anything, you foolish lass". You both laugh thinking about it.
"I think you're right", you tell your sister. "I think it would be nice to go there."
So you pack your bags, and you go to revisit a place that once made you happy - and hoping to create new memories, too.
COMMANDS: Type "help" to access the help instructions.
