A Guest Room
It's your small, cozy room in the motel. The comfortable bed is next to the window which has a view to the mountains.
You can see a dog biscuit, a bed and skis.
You can go down.
> take skis

> take skis
You came here to ski, so you pack your equipment and put them on your shoulder.
> take dog biscuit

> take dog biscuit
You take the biscuit and put it in your pocket. Maybe your sister will get hungry later.
> down

> down
You exit the bedroom and walk down the stairs to the lounge.

A Motel Lounge
It's the motel's lounge. People are drinking warm beverages and eating nutritious food and listening to the radio.
You can see a man, a cupboard and your Sister.
You can go up or outside.
> open cupboard

> open cupboard
You open the cupboard and it creaks a bit.
The cupboard contains various tools and wooden shelves filled with items, including a peanut butter jar and a shovel.

It contains a shovel and a peanut butter jar.
> take shovel

> take shovel
You pick it up.
> take peanut butter

> take peanut butter
You save it for later.
> go outside

> go outside
You leave the motel.

Outside the Motel
Walking outside, you feel the thick snow under your boots and see, in the horizon, the beautiful landscape of the Alps. You breathe the cold air into your lungs and it feels familiar. It feels like home.
You can see a pile of snow.
You can go to the Mountains, the lounge or Lake.
> dig snow

> dig snow
You grab your newly found shovel and dig the snow out of the way. Now you can go to the lake.
> go mountains

> go mountains

The Mountains
The Alps are beautiful and you feel like you'll never get tired of them. After climbing up a hill, you feel tempted to slide down on it. Down the hill you see picture-perfect pure snow. Perfect for skiing.
You can see a hill.
You can go Down the Hill or Outside.
> go down the hill

> go down the hill
 Fitting the skis on your feet and grabbing the poles, you slide down the mountain and have a load of fun. What a nice, refreshing day!

Down the Hill
After sliding down the hill, you find a lost dog in the snow. It's white, fuzzy, and rather giant.
You can see Sebastian.
You can go Mountains.
> use peanut butter on sebastian

> use peanut butter on sebastian

You open the jar, take a little bit of peanut butter and share it with Sebastian... And this good boy sure enjoys it! It wags his tail enthusiastically while licking all over your fingers. You're friends now!
Sebastian is now following you.
