A Motel Lounge
It's the motel's lounge. People are drinking warm beverages and eating nutritious food and listening to the radio.
You can see a man, a cupboard and your Sister.
You can go up or outside.
The man sees you arrive with the dogs and grins with joy. "You found my puppies! Thank you!". The dogs also run to him excitedly.
You and your sister share eye contact and smile. "I guess coming here was really worth it", you say. "Not just for us, but for Pete and the puppies, too."
"I sign under that", says your new friend.
"I'm glad we came", you say.
So you and your sister spend the rest of the winter holidays in the mountains, not alone but with your new friends. You go skiing, playing in the snow and generally enjoying each other's company and new adventures: once again, having the time of your life.

THE END

